  "answer": "**Iqbal's *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, Chapter 1 (\"Chamak teri ayaan bijli mein, aatish mein, sharare mein\") begins with the following line in English translation:**\n\n\"Your splendor is manifest in lightning, in fire, in the spark's bright glare,\"[^1]\n\nThis is the first line of the opening stanza (paragraph [p-205b95]). The chapter title reflects the opening line in Urdu transliteration.[^2]\n\n[^1]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, Chapter 1, [paragraph](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/01-chamak-teri-ayaan-bijli-mein-aatish-mein-sharare-m/translation/#p-205b95).\n\n[^2]: Allama Iqbal, *Bang-E-Dara Part 2*, Chapter 1, [chapter](/works/allama-iqbal-bang-e-dara-part-2-9bc58c/01-chamak-teri-ayaan-bijli-mein-aatish-mein-sharare-m/translation/).",
